snippet.title: MSX Flight Path 737 (MSX1, Anirog 1985)
snippet.description: This is an early flight simulator released for nearly every home computer platform in the 1980s, so the MSX was no exception. It's quite hard in the sense that the parameters are very strict (ie "can't rise landing gear below 300 feet altitude") and every minor numerical parameter exceeded results in game over/restart. It actually has a goal (fly over some mountains, in each level the mountains are higher). I was able to actually land at 3:52 of video.
